!! Introduction
When reading, you will find a lot of opinions on the issue of marriage and divorce. There is no way we can cover everything in these sermons. There is no way we can comprehend everything.

One book: "Marriage, Divorce, and Remarriage" It is not just about divorce but a significant of time is placed into marriage.

It is a super readable book. I've intended to read this book more of a reference. It is very helpful.

Last week we had the chance to look at Malachi chapter 2. We wonder what God means when God means what it is to divorce. When you are in a marriage relationship, what does that mean?

God serves as the witness and holds you accountable for the vows you've made. What is God's attitude towards marriage? In Malachi 2, God can clearly say that He hates divorce.

Last time we covered what are some permissible reasons for divorce. Due to the hardness of our hearts, there are certain circumstances where He allows divorce to take place.

Jeremiah 3 - God communicates Himself that He has written a certificate of divorce.

